Run &lt;code&gt;sudo alsamixer&lt;/code&gt;, press "F4" to chose audio input.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Make sure the right "Rear Mic" and "Capture" are enabled,
&lt;img src="http://blog.binchen.org/wp-content/linux-audio-input.png" alt="linux-audio-input.png"&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Run &lt;code&gt;alsamixer&lt;/code&gt; and check "pulseaudio" configuration in the same way.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Then test audio,
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="lang-sh"&gt;arecord --duration=5 --format=dat test-mic.wav &amp;amp;&amp;amp; aplay test-mic.wav
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>alsa</category><category>linux</category><category>sound</category><guid>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/linux-audio-input-configuration/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 15 Nov 2020 11:07:34 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>